      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">MacKinnon Parade West ¶ North Adelaide ¶ 21st October 1885 ¶ Baron Von Mueller K.C.M.G. M&amp;Ph.D. F.R.S. F.C.S ¶  ¶ &amp;c. ¶ Melbourne...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.10.21c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From David Lindsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.200/1, item 1, letter book,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pp. 398-9, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">MacKinnon Parade West</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">North Adelaide</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21st October 1885</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller K.C.M.G. M&amp;Ph.D. F.R.S. F.C.S<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very many thanks indeed for the fine parcel of useful seeds which I received per S.S. "John Elder[".]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Edge of paper damaged, end of line lost. All subsequent brackets have the same meaning. See M to D. Lindsay, 15 October 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Be assured that I shall make the best possible use of them.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You ask me to reserve one or two new<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Geograph[ic]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>localities for naming after some eminent men in Europe. I shall indeed be most happy to do so, and shall<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[be]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ever grateful to you for your numerous valuable hints and also for the interest you are taking in my expedit[ion]. I trust that we will be enabled to make a grand collect[ion]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of botanical specimens for you. I am very favora[bly]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>impressed with Lieut Dittrich and think he will prove a valuable acquisition to my party.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Compare with D. Lindsay to M, 17 December 1886.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am thankful to you for the instruction and assistance you gave him. I had already made up my party when I received his application to accompany me — and so desirous was I of taking some one who could devote his time to collecting<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>not being able to afford to purchase 2 more camels<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[and]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the necessary outfit I asked the Geographical Society to assist me. The Surveyor General<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Goyder.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who is on the Council said he believed the Govt would do<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>all [I]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wanted if I asked and recommended me to do<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[so.]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I did so, asking for the loan of two Camels and outfit and £40 for rations — this was refused — and to shame them (the Govt) into consenting I told them that I had had one Camel offered me by a poor man and £20 by you<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to D. Lindsay, 14 December 1886 (in this edition as 86-12-14a) and 21 December 1886; D. Lindsay to M, 17 December 1886 and 29 December 1886 (in this edition as 86-12-29a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as an inducement to my men to collect:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[this]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>course had the desired effect and I was very pleased<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[to]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be able to wire for Dittrich. We are taking a photographic camera and intend photographing the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>natives all through Australia. Altogether I hope to make the expedition an interesting and useful one from a scientific point of view, and if we can but find some<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[tr]aces of poor Leichardt<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Leichhardt.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>we will do a grand work.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The whole party was photographed today in bush costume and my wife will send you a copy.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Lindsay, 9 December 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very many thanks for your good wishes. [We] shall<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>leave Adelaide next monday.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You suggested that I should brand the trees with a hot iron —full name — I have a registered brand<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                    style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 14pt; ">V</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                    style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 14pt; ">
                  <hi rend="underline">79</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[on]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>my camels and I shall use that — it will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be [quite] [di]stinctive<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>enough for anything.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hoping your health is improving</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours very gratefully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>David Lindsay</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
